children.label: Distribute Application
children.classification: Cloud Migration specific / Application Migration in General
children.description: Comprises decisions regarding what parts of an application and how they are migrated. The distribution can be based on layers, tiers and components.

children.label: Select Application Layer
children.classification: Application Migration in General
children.description: Enables a selection based on the logical distribution of to be migrated application parts.

children.label: Presentation Layer
children.description: The complete presentation layer shall be migrated e.g. a web server or a rich client.

children.label: Business Layer
children.description: The complete business layer shall be migrated e.g. an application server or an ESB.

children.label: Resource Layer
children.description: The comple resource layer shall be migrated e.g. a database.

children.label: Presentation + Business Layer
children.description: The complete presentation and business layer shall be migrated.

children.label: Presentation + Resource Layer
children.description: The complete presentation and resource layer shall be migrated.

children.label: Business + Resource Layer
children.description: The complete business and resource layer shall be migrated.

children.label: Presentation + Business + Resource Layer
children.description: The complete presentation, business and resource layer shall be migrated hence the complete application.

children.label: Select Application Tier
children.classification: Application Migration in General
children.description: Enables a selection based on the physical distribution of to be migrated application parts.

children.label: Client Tier
children.description: The client tier shall be migrated or rather substituted through the application tier since a migration to the cloud will render a client tier obsolete.

children.label: Application Tier
children.description: The application tier and all the components which are running on shall be migrated.

children.label: Data Tier
children.description: The data tier and all the components which are running on shall be migrated.

children.label: Client + Application Tier
children.description: The client and applicaton tier shall be migrated.

children.label: Client + Data Tier
children.description: The client and data tier shall be migrated.

children.label: Application + Data Tier
children.description: The application and data tier shall be migrated.

children.label: Client + Application + Data Tier
children.description: The client, application and data tier shall be migrated hence the complete application.

children.label: Select Application Components
children.classification: Application Migration in General
children.description: Enables a selection based on to be migrated components according to their type and amount.

children.label: Application Component
children.description: A single application component shall be migrated e.g. an application server.

children.label: Application Components
children.description: Multiple application components shall be migrated e.g. a rich client and an ESB.

children.label: Middleware Component
children.description: A single middleware component shall be migrated e.g. a database.

children.label: Middleware Components
children.description: Multiple middleware components shall be migrated e.g. multiple databases, a caching server and a database cluster.

children.label: Application + Middleware Component
children.description: A single application and a single middleware component shall be migrated.

children.label: Application Component + Middleware Components
children.description: A single application and multiple middleware components shall be migrated.

children.label: Middleware Component + Application Components
children.description: A single middleware component and multiple application components shall be migrated.

children.label: Application + Middleware Components
children.description: Multiple application and middleware components shall be migrated.

children.label: Select Migration Type
children.classification: Cloud Migration specific
children.description: Enables selection of the kind of migration implying various constraints.

children.label: Migration Type I
children.description: Migration of a single component with IaaS, PaaS or SaaS.

children.label: Migration Type II
children.description: Migration of multiple components with IaaS, PaaS or SaaS.

children.label: Migration Type III
children.description: Migration of the whole application as-is with IaaS.

children.label: Migration Type IV
children.description: Migration of the whole application based on cloud services with PaaS or SaaS.

children.label: Define Elasticity Strategy
children.classification: Cloud Migration specific / Application Migration in General
children.description: Comprises decisions regarding which components and how they are scaled.

children.label: Define Scalability Level
children.classification: Cloud Migration specific / Application Migration in General
children.description: Enables defintion on which level the migrated component(s) will be scaled.

children.label: No Scaling
children.description: The migrated components will not have to scale.

children.label: OS/VM Level Scaling
children.description: The application shall scale on VM level e.g. by instantiating new machines or requiring more resources for existing ones.

children.label: Middleware Level Scaling
children.description: The application shall scale on the middleware level e.g. by adding or removing application servers.

children.label: Application Level Scaling
children.description: The application shall scale on the application level e.g. by adding or removing instances inside an application server.

children.label: OS/VM + Middleware Level Scaling
children.description: The application shall scale on the VM as well as on the middleware level.

children.label: OS/VM + Application Level Scaling
children.description: The application shall scale on the VM and the application level.

children.label: Middleware + Application Level Scaling
children.description: The application shall scale on the middleware and the application level.

children.label: OS/VM + Middleware + Application Level Scaling
children.description: The application shall scale on the VM, the middleware and the application level.

children.label: Select Scaling Type
children.classification: Cloud Migration specific / Application Migration in General
children.description: Enables selection if the scaled component(s) will be scaled up/out or both.

children.label: Vertical Scaling
children.description: The component shall scale up and down i.e. through adding or removing resources.

children.label: Horizontal Scaling
children.description: The component shall scale out and in i.e. adding or removing instances.

children.label: Hybrid Scaling
children.description: The component shall scale up and down as well as in and out.

children.label: Select Elasticity Automation Degree
children.classification: Cloud Migration specific / Application Migration in General
children.description: Enables selection of the automation degree of the applied scaling level and type.

children.label: Manual Scaling
children.description: The scaling shall be performed manually.

children.label: Semi-Automatic Scaling
children.description: The scaling shall be performed semi-automatically i.e. by defining tresholds which trigger defined scaling actions.

children.label: Semi-Automatic Third-Party Scaling
children.description: The scaling shall be performed semi-automatically i.e. by defining tresholds which trigger defined scaling actions and entirely performed by a third party.

children.label: Automatic Scaling
children.description: The scaling shall be fully automatic without prior manual set up.

children.label: Automatic Third-Party Scaling
children.description: The scaling shall be fully automatic without prior manual set up and entirely performed by a third party.

children.label: Select Scaling Trigger
children.classification: Cloud Migration specific / Application Migration in General
children.description: Enables selection if and how the scaling is triggered.

children.label: No Trigger
children.description: The scaling action shall not be triggered by anything. Notifications are not subsumed under triggers.

children.label: Event-Driven Trigger
children.description: The scaling shall be triggered by events e.g. exceeding thresholds.

children.label: Proactive Trigger
children.description: The scaling shall be triggered prior to the unexpected resource limitation.

children.label: Define Multi-Tenancy Requirements
children.classification: Cloud Migration specific
children.description: Comprises decision to denote if and how  multi-tenancy is supported by the migrated application.

children.label: Select Multi-Tenancy Architecture
children.classification: Cloud Migration specific
children.description: Enables selection of a specific multi-tenancy architecture.

children.label: Multi-Tenancy Architecture 0
children.description: The application stack shall only be shared between tenants on the level of infrastructure e.g. hardware, facility.

children.label: Multi-Tenancy Architecture 1
children.description: The application stack shall only be shared between tenants on the level of the operating system, virtual machines (hypervisor level) and below.

children.label: Multi-Tenancy Architecture 2
children.description: The application stack shall only be shared between tenants on the level of the middleware and below e.g. sharing the same enterprise service bus or application server.

children.label: Multi-Tenancy Architecture 3
children.description: The application stack shall be fully shared between tenantes i.e. they use the same application instance.

children.label: Select Service Provider / Offering
children.classification: Cloud Migration specific / Application Migration in General
children.description: Comprises decision concerned with essential  technical as well as organizational aspects for the cloud solution.

children.label: Select Cloud Deployment Model
children.classification: Cloud Migration specific
children.description: Enables selection which of the cloud deployment models shall be used.

children.label: Public Cloud
children.description: The application shall be deployed in a public cloud environment.

children.label: Private Cloud
children.description: The application shall be deployed in a private cloud environment.

children.label: Community Cloud
children.description: The application shall be deployed in a community cloud environment.

children.label: Hybrid Cloud
children.description: The application shall be deployed in a public and private cloud environment.

children.label: Select Cloud Service Model
children.classification: Cloud Migration specific
children.description: Enables selection which of the cloud service models shall be used.

children.label: IaaS
children.description: The application shall use a Infrastructure as a Service offering.

children.label: PaaS
children.description: The application shall use a Platforma as a Service offering.

children.label: SaaS
children.description: The application shall use a Software as a Service offering.

children.label: IaaS + PaaS
children.description: The application shall use a combination of IaaS and PaaS offering.

children.label: IaaS + SaaS
children.description: The application shall use a combination of PaaS and SaaS offering.

children.label: PaaS + SaaS
children.description: The application shall use a combination of IaaS and SaaS offering.

children.label: Iaas + PaaS + SaaS
children.description: The application shall use a combination of Iaas, PaaS and SaaS offering.

children.label: Define Cloud Hosting
children.classification: Cloud Migration specific / Application Migration in General
children.description: Enables selection where the cloud application will be hosted.

children.label: On-Premise Hosting
children.description: The application shall be hosted on-premise.

children.label: Off-Premise Hosting
children.description: The application shall be hosted off-premise.

children.label: Hybrid Hosting
children.description: The applicaton shall be hosted on- as well as off-premise.

children.label: Define Roles of Responsibility
children.classification: Cloud Migration specific / Application Migration in General
children.description: Enables selection of organizational responsibility for ownership, operation and management.

children.label: Role Set 1
children.description: The hardware is owned by the company which also operates and manages the migrated cloud application and environment.

children.label: Role Set 7
children.description: The cloud environment and the underlying hardware is owned and operated by a third party whereas the cloud application is managed by the company.

children.label: Role Set 8
children.description: The hardware and the cloud environment is owned and operated by a third party which also manages the application.

children.label: Role Set 1 + 7
children.description: Combination of Role Set 1 and 7.

children.label: Role Set 1 + 8
children.description: Combination of Role Set 1 and 8.

children.label: Role Set 7 + 8
children.description: Combination of Role Set 7 and 8.

children.label: Role Set 1 + 7 + 8
children.description: Combination of Role Set 1, 7 and 8.

children.label: Select Cloud Vendor
children.classification: Cloud Migration specific / Application Migration in General
children.description: Decision stands for a cloud vendor such as Amazon, Microsoft or Google.

children.label: Evaluated Cloud Vendor
children.description: Evaluated cloud vendor which has to be determined through a vendor benchmark and selection.

children.label: Select Pricing Model
children.classification: Cloud Migration specific
children.description: Enables selection of a pricing scheme for the used cloud resources.

children.label: Free
children.description: Denotes freely offered serivces through cloud vendors.

children.label: Pay-Per-Use
children.description: The application usage shall be charged on a pay-per-use basis e.g. cent per gigabyte of occupied storage over a specific time.

children.label: Pay-Per-Unit
children.description: The application usage shall be charged on a pay-per-unit basis

children.label: Charge-Per-Use (Subscription)
children.description: The application usage shall be charded on a subscription basis e.g. upfront payment for the use to specific terms and conditions.

children.label: Combined Pricing Model
children.description: The application shall use a combination of pricing models.

children.label: Define Resource Location
children.classification: Cloud Migration specific / Application Migration in General
children.description: Enables selection of geographical position in relation to the jurisdiction of the company.

children.label: Data Location under same jurisdiction as company
children.description: The data location has to be under the same jurisdiction as the company at all time to keep data security laws enforced.

children.label: Data Location outside jurisdiction of company
children.description: The data location can be under a different jurisdiction than the company is and hence data is allowed to fall under country or region specific laws and regulations.
